A nine-year study by the University of Calgary revealed that grizzly bears near Banff National Park have the lowest birth rate in North America.
This study includes policy recommendations and aims to protect the bears.
Plans to remove grizzlies from the endangered species list in the Yellowstone region have sparked debate.
While some see it as a success story, others worry about the impact on critical habitats.
The population of Yellowstone grizzlies has rebounded significantly, leading to discussions about delisting and potential hunting regulations.
Despite differing opinions, the focus remains on preserving the bears' habitat for future generations.
